This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it proposes a novel deep architecture for sequence-to-sequence learning, which is a common task in natural language processing. The paper also mentions machine translation, which is a subfield of computational linguistics. 

The paper also involves deep learning techniques, which makes it likely to belong to the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

The use of memories and read-write operations in the architecture suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). 

Finally, the paper mentions the use of the architecture for image captioning, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category cs.CV (Computer Vision).
